the principal divisions of the funds were :    $ 700,000 to the university of california for the construction of an observatory and the placing therein of a telescope to be more powerful than any other in existence   $ 150,000 for the building and maintenance of free public james lick baths in san francisco   $ 540,000 to found and endow an institution of san francisco to be known as the california school of mechanic arts   $ 100,000 for the erection of three appropriate groups of bronze statuary to represent three periods in californian history and to be placed before the city hall of san francisco   $ 60,000 to erect in golden gate park , san francisco , a memorial to francis scott key , author of   â€œ

